      {
        "id": "745911e7eccbeb79d1cfd274f2f2f1ba244da19e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-19 12:40:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThat oom variable substitution is what will break spring – it looks like a the nodeport was not tested and ctxBuilderExternapPort is not named properly or it is missing or mis-spelled in values.yaml in the sub chart \ncheck the oom patch for sdnc\n\n\"{{ .Values.config.ctxBuilderExternalPort }}\"\n\nthen check all the already merged code that calls the sdnc-ctx – that they have been retrofitted to call the new sdnc container properly.\n\n\nFor the sdnc (target) patch there is no external node port 302xx – as expected because we use the pomba k8s service name inside the pod\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/55451/9/kubernetes/pomba/charts/pomba-sdncctxbuilder/templates/deployment.yaml\n\nCheck that the variable in the calling service is using 9530 and the dns name in the calling chart that references sdnc-ctx-builder – defined below\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/55451/1/kubernetes/pomba/charts/pomba-sdncctxbuilder/values.yaml \n\n\nFrom: J.Ram  \nSent: Thursday, October 18, 2018 10:17 PM\nCc: *\nSubject: “BugFix: missing variable in SDNC OOM” -- Fixed\n\n1126\n\nThe SDNC CtxBuilder is having logging issues. \nI seem to have a problem in the CTX Agg, with the below error: \n\n2018-10-19 01:47:39,352|||pool-2-thread-2||||ERROR||||||| Error getting result from sdnc context builder.  Reason - For input string: \"{{ .Values.config.ctxBuilderExternalPort }}\"\n2018-10-19 01:47:39,352|||pool-2-thread-2||||INFO||||||| Error returned from one of the Context builders, no event will be published.\n\n1.\tThe defect above shows that the logging is not configured properly for sdnc ctx builder as it is deployed with aai-ctx-builder logging.  And there is 0 logs to show any information from the error above \n2.\tThe actual error, I think is a separate bug.  Designers please advise ( from point 1, I cannot say what the real issue is)",
        "patchset_number": 9
      },
      {
        "id": "7b23b029e06c6935f048016f60f33f110142e5c6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-19 12:48:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 9: -Code-Review\n\nThat oom variable substitution is likely the issue – it looks like the service port (from incoming containers) has property resolution issues and ctxBuilderExternalPort is not named properly or it is missing or mis-spelled in values.yaml in the sub chart \n\nTpl macros should not show up in runtime code – they should be resolved by then.\ncheck the oom patch for sdnc\n\n\"{{ .Values.config.ctxBuilderExternalPort }}\"\n\nthen check all the already merged code that calls the sdnc-ctx – that they have been retrofitted to call the new sdnc container properly.",
        "patchset_number": 9
      },
